## What's Happening

The `Console` CR (`console.streamshub.github.com`) does **not exist** in the cluster — only the OpenShift built-in `console.config.openshift.io` exists. This means the **StreamsHub Console operator is NOT managing the secret**. 

The secret `dev-console-console-secret` was **created manually** and contains the config directly. Your Helm `kafka-console.yaml` template creates a `Console` CR but that CR is either not being applied or the operator is not installed.

The secret still has the wrong URL:
```
url: "https://thanos-querier-openshift-monitoring.apps.dev.sbiepay.sbi"  ← WRONG
```

---

## The Direct Fix — Update Secret via Helm in Pipeline

In your `kafka-console.yaml` template, **add a Secret resource** that Helm will manage directly. Add this to the file:

```yaml
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
  name: dev-console-console-secret
  namespace: {{ .Values.console.namespace }}
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}
  annotations:
    meta.helm.sh/release-name: {{ .Release.Name }}
    meta.helm.sh/release-namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}
type: Opaque
stringData:
  console-config.yaml: |
    ---
    kubernetes:
      enabled: true
    security:
      subjects: []
      roles: []
      audit: []
      oidc: null
    metricsSources:
    - name: "kafka-metrics"
      type: "openshift-monitoring"
      url: {{ .Values.console.metrics.prometheus.url | quote }}
    schemaRegistries: []
    kafka:
      clusters:
      - name: {{ .Values.console.kafkaClusters.name | quote }}
        namespace: {{ .Values.console.kafkaClusters.namespace | quote }}
        listener: {{ .Values.console.listener | quote }}
        security:
          subjects: []
          roles: []
          audit: []
        properties:
          security.protocol: "PLAINTEXT"
          bootstrap.servers: "{{ .Values.console.kafkaClusters.name }}-kafka-bootstrap.{{ .Values.console.kafkaClusters.namespace }}.svc:9092"
        adminProperties:
          security.protocol: "PLAINTEXT"
          request.timeout.ms: "30000"
          default.api.timeout.ms: "30000"
        consumerProperties:
          security.protocol: "PLAINTEXT"
          request.timeout.ms: "30000"
        producerProperties:
          security.protocol: "PLAINTEXT"
          request.timeout.ms: "30000"
```

This way when the pipeline runs `helm upgrade`, it will update the secret with the correct Prometheus URL from `values.yaml`.

